    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tail-on-prawn-courgette-and-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> into discs</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tail-on-prawn-courgette-and-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced courgette </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until the courgette has begun to brown and soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tail-on-prawn-courgette-and-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>spinach & ricotta ravioli</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook your <strong>ravioli </strong>for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the ravioli, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tail-on-prawn-courgette-and-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the courgette has softened, add your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic </strong>to the pan with a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tail-on-prawn-courgette-and-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>tail on jumbo prawns</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> tail on jumbo prawns </strong>and cook for 7-8 min or until the prawns are cooked through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tail-on-prawn-courgette-and-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the prawns are cooked, remove the pan from the heat and add the <strong>drained ravioli </strong>and your <strong>cr\u00e8me fra\u00eeche</strong></p><p>Add a splash of the <strong>starchy pasta water </strong>and gently stir it all together until the pasta is coated in the sauce and season to taste \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy jumbo tail on prawn, courgette and spinach & ricotta ravioli</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-tail-on-prawn-courgette-and-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy jumbo tail on prawn, courgette and spinach & ricotta ravioli</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
